# Security Best Practices

## Configuration Security
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Never hardcode credentials
- Never commit sensitive data
- Use [appsettings.json.template](mdc:OutlineMCP/appsettings.json.template) as base

## Input Validation
- Validate all user input
- Use Data Annotations or FluentValidation
- Sanitize outputs
- Handle secrets properly

## API Security
- Use secure communication (HTTPS)
- Validate all API responses
- Handle rate limiting
- Implement retry policies

## Logging Security
- Do not log sensitive data
- Use structured logging
- Include correlation IDs
- Log appropriate detail levels

## Authentication
- Use built-in ASP.NET Core Identity when possible
- Validate API tokens at startup
- Handle authentication errors gracefully
